post_text: Thank you to our CES staff for making us smile :-)
text: Thank you to our CES staff for making us smile :-)

shared_text:
Kennett Drumline
May 11 at 10:42 AM ¬∑

Hi everyone, We hope you are all staying healthy! What have we been up to? Well, remote learning has been different, for sure, but we are still actively learning to improve our drumming skills. One of our assignments was a study on syncopated rhythms. "What are syncopated rhythms," you might ask? Well, syncopation happens when rhythms are played in unexpected ways by shifting the placement of the most important notes. Syncopation helps make rhythms interesting and unpredictable. After we learned to play some syncopated rhythms, we had Google meetings by sections (snare drums, bass drums, quad (tenor) drums, and cymbals). Each section created syncopated rhythms, combining and adapting the rhythms we studied, without knowing what the other sections were composing. Then Dr. Davison entered them into a computer program to hear the resulting composition. We are excited to present, for the first time ever, our Socially Distant Groove. We plan to play it (live and in person) year after year in the future. ü•Å PLEASE LISTEN AND ENJOY!

post_text: Governor Sununu announced this afternoon that remote instruction in NH will continue for the rest of the school year. April vacation for students will take place from April 27-May 1. Food Service will provide 3 sets of meals on April 24 and another 3 sets of meals on April 29. The last student day in Conway and Bartlett will be June 15. the last student day in Jackson will be June 12. Continue to check www.sau9.org for updates and information.

Kennett High School- New Hampshire
March 27 at 6:58 AM ¬∑

So here it is! The Kennett High School Spirit Challenge. We are asking all students, staff, and even alum to post a picture in comments section of yourself wearing your KHS gear, or wearing the school colors. The easiest way to do this is to through your mobile device. Go to your photos, select the one you want to share, then go to the comment section of this post and hit paste. Please do not put any names in your post, just the picture. Every student and staff that post will be entered in a drawing for a prize. Winners will be selected on Monday. We are so excited to see you all!
